---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lang = 'en';
const title = "AI Notes — April 11";
const date = "2026-04-11";
---

<Layout title={title} lang={lang}>
  <div class="container">
    <article class="article">
      <div class="article-header fade-in">
        <a href="/writing/" class="back-link">← Back to Writing</a>
        <div class="article-meta">
          <span class="tag">Learning Log</span>
          <time datetime={date}>April 11, 2026</time>
        </div>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="article-body fade-in">
        <h2>How to Arrange Agents</h2>
        <p>Agent execution should work like a well-run organization. Consultant-style coordination is becoming a first-class design pattern: a "cheap executor + expensive consultant" combination. The key insight: use fast models for most steps, only escalate complexity when decisions are hard.</p>
        <p>Haiku + Opus combination reportedly doubled BrowseComp scores compared to Haiku alone. Sonnet + Opus combination reduces task cost while improving SWE-bench multilingual scores. This pattern is being rapidly adopted in open-source: LangChain DeepAgents implemented consultant middleware.</p>
        <p>The direction agents are evolving: increasingly like fast worker models, delegating complex decisions to "intelligent advisors."</p>

        <h2>Claude for Word</h2>
        <p>This could erode Microsoft's own business.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .article { max-width: 680px; padding-bottom: 3rem; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .back-link { display: inline-block; color: var(--color-text-muted); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; transition: color var(--transition); }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .article-meta { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .article-meta time { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  .article-header h1 { font-size: 2rem; line-height: 1.3; letter-spacing: -0.03em; }
  .article-body { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.85; color: var(--color-text); }
  .article-body h2 { font-size: 1.35rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .article-body p { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); }
  .article-body ul { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  .article-body li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.75; }
  .article-body strong { color: var(--color-text); font-weight: 600; }
  .article-body pre { background: var(--color-card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.25rem; overflow-x: auto; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .article-body code { font-size: 0.9em; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .article-header h1 { font-size: 1.5rem; } }
</style>